        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Salute Rufus chosen in the Lord, and his mother and mine",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Observe the graceful way in which St. Paul intimates his obligation to the mother of Rufus, who at some time (though when and where we know not) had been as a mother to himself. Similar delicate courtesy of language is especially observable in the Epistle to Philemon. Romans 16:13",
        "children": []
      },
